        "#Chapter 2 - Fundamentals of Unconstrained Optimization\n",
        "\n",
        "##2.1 - What is a solution?\n",
        "\n",
        "*Def*: A point $x^*$ is a global minimizer if $f(x^*) \\leq f(x) \\space \\forall x \\epsilon \\mathbb{R}^n $.\n",
        "\n",
        "*Def*: A point $x^*$ is a (weak) local minimizer if $\\exists \\mathcal{N} s.t. f(x^*) <= f(x) \\space \\forall x \\epsilon \\mathcal{N}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "*Def*: A point $x^*$ is a strict (strong) local minimizer if $\\exists \\mathcal{N} s.t. f(x^*) < f(x) \\space \\forall x \\epsilon \\mathcal{N}$ with $x \\neq x^*$."
      ]
    }
  ]
}